Brown ground beef in 12-inch skillet; drain. Stir in Pasta Sauce and water. Bring to a boil over high heat. Stir in uncooked rotini and return to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook covered, stirring occasionally, 12 minutes or until rotini is tender. Remove from heat and sprinkle with cheese. Cover and let stand 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.